subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. This species can be distinguished from all other Neotropical 

Xanthopimpla

by the combination of the following characters: 
1
) occipital carina incomplete, expanded into a high thin flange only basally; 
2
) posterior transverse carina bowed in the center; 
3
) ovipositor with 
11
teeth on lower valve; and 
4
) ovipositor sheath about 
0.9 to 1.2
times as long as hind tibia.
